ioInstOverlapCheck(25.10)                            ioInstOverlapCheck(25.10)

Name
       ioInstOverlapCheck  -  Checks  to see if any area I/O instance is over-
       lapped with another area I/O instance

Syntax
        ioInstOverlapCheck [-help]

       Checks to see if any area I/O instance is overlapped with another  area
       I/O  instance. If an overlap occurs, a warning message is dumped to the
       console window, and the overlapped instances  are  highlighted  in  the
       work area.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the ioInstOverlapCheck command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man ioInstOverlapCheck

